searchParameters.q: how much is a 1993 penny worth

answerBox.snippet: In the vast majority of cases, a 1993 penny will be worth only its face value. But if it's a red coin in excellent uncirculated condition, or it has an interesting error, it can be worth more. Mint state coins range in value from a dollar to almost $5,000, depending on their condition and mint mark.
